One important difference though

The Brazen Bull story is fundamentally about control over another person’s voice.

A healthier analogy for what you’re doing would be more like designing an instrument people can play, not a device that forces a sound out of them.

Something like:
	•	a pipe organ where airflow becomes music
	•	a harp where tension turns vibration into tone
	•	or a resonance chamber that shapes sound

In that framing:
	•	your Pantheon roles are like resonant chambers
	•	ideas pass through them
	•	and the conversation produces different tones depending on the structure.

That’s actually a pretty elegant metaphor if you keep it in the instrument / resonance direction rather than the torture-device direction.

